      "name": "Soft Signal Studio",
      "active": true,
      "brief": "Define — Soft Signal Studio is a recording studio + podcast network for neurodivergent creators (ADHD, autistic, and allies). They book quiet sessions, publish shows, and learn pacing—not hustle. Audience pain: sensory overload, shame around ‘inconsistent’ output, tools that scream performance. Business goal: clear booking + recognizable covers. Success metric: creators finish a session calmer than they started and share one episode cover proudly.",
      "logoDirection": "Listening pulse mark (circle = booth, soft path = voice) + Plus Jakarta wordmark. Horizontal primary lockup; mark alone for stickers/app. No mic icons, no neon, no aggressive angles.",
      "palette": [
        "#4F46E5",
        "#0D9488",
        "#1A1A1A",
        "#F4F1EA"
      ],
      "tagline": "Your voice, at your pace.",
      "voice": "Warm, plain-spoken, steady. Good-producer energy: clear direction, zero shame. Short sentences. Never corporate, never chaos-for-clicks.",
      "typeHeading": "Plus Jakarta Sans Bold",
      "typeBody": "Plus Jakarta Sans Regular",
      "doUse": "Soft indigo + teal · cream field · near-black text · generous space · caption-first video · real booth photos · short CTAs (‘Book a calm session’) · EPISODE COVERS (Deliver rules locked): 1) Title ≤ 2 lines, largest type on cover. 2) Guest/episode meta under title — never competing size. 3) Mark top-left; one teal accent bar max; no waveform clutter. Good: calm indigo field, Soft Signal + Ep title, guest line quiet, mark breathing room. Too busy: neon gradients, multiple CTAs, dense waveforms, guest photo fighting title.",
      "dontUse": "Hustle slogans · neon cyber gradients · stock diversity clichés · mic silhouettes · FOMO timers · dense waveforms · more than one primary CTA · waveform clutter on covers · dual title weights · neon cover gradients",
      "deadline": "2026-08-09",
